    {
      "id": "42d7ecfd_a99bfe14",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/rest/ApiRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 211,
      "message": "Yes I agree - the integration team should be able via the K8S charts to override default logback.xml to provide more details if necessary. We had Chenfei add these because I believe there really were none to begin with (I think that's what it was - I could be wrong). Now that the code is more stable, we can change these to what we would expect in production. The returned HTTP error codes should be enough, along with perhaps changing the error message payload to be more descriptive. I noticed some of the error messages being returned had no JSON format. Perhaps we re-visit that.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 57,
        "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pd1248@att.com",
        "username": "pdragosh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-02 15:40:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "c73b9a44_34dbf959",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "820b1e9f_970752a6",
      "file_path": "main/src/test/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/rest/TestApiRestServer.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 570,
      "message": "Yes fine with me.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 57,
        "name": "Pamela Dragosh",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "pd1248@att.com",
        "username": "pdragosh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-02 15:40:57.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "46c51ec8_be08e4e9",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "b5a6e0de_50b5a672",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/rest/ApiRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 211,
      "message": "Yeah. I added this just for testing with CLAMP when the code was initially built and less stable. I am fine with either leave it and rely on integration team to override logback to have more verbosed msgs or remove logging this per prod requirement. The descriptive msg is already packaged with returned code in \"pfme\" that is passed into \"makeErrorResponse\".",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1441,
        "name": "Chenfei Gao",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "cgao@research.att.com",
        "username": "cgao"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-02 16:06:53.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "42d7ecfd_a99bfe14",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "2d63bdf5_0ecda3fd",
      "file_path": "main/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/api/main/rest/ApiRestController.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 211,
      "message": "There are 2 aspects: 1) how to categorize logging messages, and 2) default logging level at labs.  \n\nRegarding 2) I agree, would want to go out at WARN default logging level as default configuration\n\nRegarding 1), the jump from error to debug is high.   To me, it will fit best the info level, as I think it has importance, more than for example, that printing every incoming byte in the wire as the apache http client library does, that will be put together in the same category.\n\nIf the issue is analyzable somewhat postmortem by some other means in the http respose as Pam and Chenfei are pointing out, I could be with it, although the message categorization as debug does not seem right to me.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 477,
        "name": "Jorge Hernandez",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jorge.hernandez-herrero@att.com",
        "username": "jhh"
      },
      "updated": "2020-01-02 17:01:46.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "b5a6e0de_50b5a672",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
